                <h1>How Long Does a CWOF Stay on Your Record?</h1>
                <p>A Conditional Warrant of Fitness (CWOF) typically stays on your driving record for 3 years from the date of issuance. During this time, it can impact your insurance rates and driving privileges. After 3 years, it may be removed, but some jurisdictions have different rules, so check local regulations for specifics.</p>
